    "This would imply that, one of the main sources of bias in the output are the datasets used as an input, referred to as dataset bias.",
    "We want to emphasize that reducing the problem solely to a matter of data bias is an oversimplification since such a reduction neglects the intricate web of factors underlying these biases, including historical legacies and societal injustices (Birhane, 2021).",
    "However, given that an in-depth discussion of historical and societal injustices is out of the scope of this chapter, we will further zoom in on data bias where we distinguish between coverage and social bias.",
